eNCA's Aviwe Mtila has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former workers at the Royal Bafokeng Platinum Mine say they have been forcefully removed from their accommodation. They say court proceedings for dismissal are still underway so they do not understand why they are being removed from their homes. READ: Crime in SA | WATCH | Illegal mining on the rise The mine says the houses are in a development for employees and some had been rented out unlawfully. The platinum mine says it has been trying for three years to find another solution.